  <h1>
   audio_get_type
  </h1>
  When adding audio to
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  it can be either
  <i>
   streamed
  </i>
  or
  <i>
   in memory
  </i>
  . If you need to know whether a given sound index is for streamed audio or not you can
    use this function which will return 1 for streamed, 0 for sound in memory, and -1 if there is any error or the index does not point to a valid sound resource.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">audio_get_type(index);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      index
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Sounds.htm">
        Sound Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the sound to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">type = audio_get_type(snd_Music_1);
</code></pre>
  The above code checks the type of audio indexed in the variable "snd_Music_1" and stores the returned value in the variable "type".
 </body>
</html>